         - Extracts method, path, version from request line
         - Parses headers (case-insensitive keys)
         - Separates body at \r\n\r\n
         - Handles query strings from URL
       4. Lookup Helpers
         - chttp_query_param(req, key) - Find query param by key
         - chttp_header(req, key) - Find header by key (case-insensitive)
         - chttp_path_param(req, name) - Find path param by name
       5. Path Parameter Matching (chttp_match_route)
         - Pattern: /users/:id matches /users/123, captures id=123
         - Supports wildcard segments starting with :
         - Exact segment matching for literal parts
       6. Routing (chttp_route, chttp_ws_route, chttp_sse_route)
         - Registers routes with method, pattern, and handler
         - Returns -1 if route table full (max 64)
       7. WebSocket Support
         - SHA-1 hashing (RFC 3174) for WS handshake
         - Base64 encoding for Sec-WebSocket-Accept
         - WebSocket frames: Unmasked frames (server→client), masked frames (client→server)
         - chttp_ws_send() - Send unmasked text frame
