       Function: fork_and_run(req, res, handler, username)

       Flow:
       1. Look up user info via getpwnam_r() (reentrant)
       2. Create pipe for EOF-based child exit detection
       3. Fork process:
         - Child:
             - Close listening socket (g_server_fd)
           - Drop supplementary groups via initgroups()
           - Set GID via setgid()
           - Set UID via setuid() (irreversible check: setuid(0) should fail)
           - chdir() to user home (fallback to /tmp)
           - Call handler
           - Write response to client socket
           - Close pipe write-end (signals parent EOF)
           - _exit(0)
         - Parent:
             - Close pipe write-end
           - select() on pipe read-end with 30s timeout
           - If timeout: SIGKILL child, send 504 Gateway Timeout
           - waitpid() to reap zombie
           - Set res->status = 0 (sentinel: "already sent response")

